 I started my journey into full-time ministry

12
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,720
 as a youth pastor.

13
00:00:25,720 --> 00:00:28,000
 And back then I was serving the church I grew up in

14
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,080
 over in Kowloon Tong.

15
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,840
 I see Paco right there actually.

16
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:32,080
 You was in my youth group.

17
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:34,200
 Okay, well I'm talking about you, okay Paco.

18
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:38,320
 Anyway, so I was the youth pastor for a little while.

19
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:42,440
 And youth work is a great way to get to know

20
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:43,920
 how to do ministry.

21
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:46,440
 And one of the things I got to do was to take

22
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:48,320
 youth groups on mission trips.

23
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:50,960
 And so this was about 17 years ago.

24
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:52,660
 I was just a kid back then.

25
00:00:52,660 --> 00:00:55,680
 So I was like a big kid taking some little kids

26
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:58,580
 to a foreign country, a place I didn't know the language,

27
00:00:58,580 --> 00:01:00,960
 I didn't know the people to serve a group.

28
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,240
 I didn't even really know who I was connecting with.

29
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:05,480
 It's amazing that the parents allowed this all to happen

30
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,520
 in the first place, right?

31
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:11,600
 But it was a really good trip actually overall.

32
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,400
 But on the first night when we got there,

33
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:15,760
 we were looking for a place to have dinner.

34
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,240
 Okay, actually we were in Hainan Island.

35
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,520
 This is when I discovered that Hainanese chicken rice

36
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:21,920
 is not really from Hainan Island, okay.

37
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,320
 Amongst many other things.

38
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,960
 So we were looking for a place to have dinner.

39
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:27,560
 I was walking around with me and a bunch of about

40
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:30,920
 12 other kids, teenagers, preteens.

41
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,380
 And so we found this place, right.

42
00:01:32,380 --> 00:01:34,120
 It was a cheap hot pot place.

43
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,020
 So I thought, perfect, you know.

44
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:39,760
 Hong Kong kids, cheap hot pot, perfect place for dinner.

45
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:42,240
 Right, and so we decided to have dinner there.

46
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,860
 And when we walked in, we discovered actually

47
00:01:43,860 --> 00:01:46,500
 it's a all you can eat place.

48
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,640
 So yeah, right, we love that, right.

49
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:53,520
 But how it worked was you get one visit to the buffet table,

50
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:54,840
 you get as much food as you want,

51
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,560
 and you can bring it back to the table,

52
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:58,800
 and that was your dinner.

53
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,120
 Okay, so we were all there having good time

54
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:04,120
 and eating away, and there was one kid though

55
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,920
 who got way too much food.

56
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:08,240
 Like it was just like a ridiculous amount of food.

57
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,160
 Do you remember back in the day,

58
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,160
 or back when I was growing up, Pizza Hut, right,

59
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:14,320
 had the salad bar, right.

60
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:16,680
 Oh, Pizza Hut salad bar, right.

61
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,960
 Me going out for Pizza Hut was like, yes, you know,

62
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,720
 Saitan, you know, white people food, right.

63
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,880
 This is amazing, okay.

64
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:25,780
 But that salad bar, right, you got that really flimsy,

65
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:28,760
 brown, like bamboo-ish sort of bowl, do you remember that?

66
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:30,280
 Right, and there was whole art to like

67
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,880
 building up the salad, right.

68
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,800
 So you put like the potatoes at the bottom

69
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,360
 to get like a foundation, right.

70
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,960
 Stick some cucumbers on the side

71
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:39,920
 so you could like widen the bowl a little bit, right.

72
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,120
 And people would come back,

73
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:44,180
 and it was like this huge tower of salad, right.

74
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:46,120
 But in the end, like, it just got wasted

75
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,040
 'cause it was disgusting.

76
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,320
 It was like Thousand Island sauce

77
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:50,280
 over like pineapples and raisins,

78
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:53,200
 and like all this random stuff mashed together.

79
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,400
 It was disgusting.

80
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,760
 No one actually liked the salad,

81
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,600
 and I think they just like seeing how tall

82
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,000
 they could make that tower, right,

83
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,760
 and bringing it back to the table.

84
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,140
 Well, that's kind of what happened, right.

85
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,940
 This kid got all this food, right.

86
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:06,100
 There was so much, so much food that he got.

87
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,020
 He couldn't finish it all.

88
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:09,200
 And so I got really upset.

89
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,000
 I was like, what are we gonna do, right?

90
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,280
 You've wasted all this food.

91
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,520
 But then I also thought to myself,

92
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:18,440
 okay, there's a teachable moment here, all right.

93
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:21,400
 How am I gonna make this into a life lesson, right?

94
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,240
 So it's a true story.

95
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,080
 This is what I did.

96
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:24,080
 I told the young guy, he's like,

97
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:25,600
 dude, like what happened?

98
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,840
 You just wasted all this food.

99
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,880
 And he said to me, yeah, I thought

100
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,320
 it was all you can eat, Allison.

101
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,680
 So well, yeah, all you can eat

102
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,680
 doesn't mean all you can waste, okay.

103
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:36,000
 So like, what are we gonna do about this?

104
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,200
 You know, you didn't eat the food.

105
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:39,240
 You're gonna have to pay for it now.

106
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,480
 And he starts to panic.

107
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,220
 He's like, well, I didn't do anything wrong, right.

108
00:03:42,220 --> 00:03:43,280
 You said it was all you can eat.

109
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,520
 I'm just gonna put the food back.

110
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,240
 He's like, dude, that's disgusting, okay.

111
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,140
 Do not put the food back, okay.

112
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:49,960
 It's at the table now, all right.

113
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,360
 Something's gotta happen.

114
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,640
 And he said, what's gonna happen?

115
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:55,240
 So I told him, okay, well, the manager's gonna come.

116
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,140
 He's gonna weigh all the food.

117
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,540
 And according to how much it weighs,

118
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,240
 you're gonna have to pay the penalty

119
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,560
 for wasting all this food.

120
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:05,060
 And then he really starts to panic.

121
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,960
 So how much money are you gonna have to pay?

122
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,000
 Like, my mom didn't give me that much pocket money.

123
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,800
 You know, I've been planning to spend on some souvenirs.

124
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,800
 Like, I don't have it.

125
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,840
 Like, what am I gonna do?

126
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:17,020
 So I told him, okay, the only way you can get out of this

127
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:18,760
 is if you go to the manager

128
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,280
 and you beg him for forgiveness, okay.

129
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:22,640
 Beg him for forgiveness.

130
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:24,960
 Maybe he'll just let you go.

131
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,800
 He's panicking, okay, where is he?

132
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,160
 So I point to a gentleman

133
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,560
 sitting on the other side of the restaurant, okay.

134
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:32,320
 That's the manager sitting right there, right.

135
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:35,040
 Now, I've just pointed to a random guy

136
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,440
 minding his business, okay.

137
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:38,660
 He's there having dinner with his family, right.

138
00:04:38,660 --> 00:04:42,360
 Because the truth was, there was no manager, okay.

139
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,640
 It was mad at him.

140
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,540
 I, just like I said, teachable moment.

141
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:48,740
 I wanted to teach him a lesson to not to waste food.

142
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:51,360
 Right, so this boy, he stands there for a minute, right.

143
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,600
 And he's like sweating bullets.

144
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,680
 He's like rehearsing what he's gonna say.

145
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,800
 You know, practicing his Mandarin.

146
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,680
 He's like, (mimics Mandarin)

147
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,360
 Right, and so, and then he really like, you know,

148
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:02,080
 coyly walks up to this man, taps him on the shoulder,

149
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,280
 and he just starts going for it.

150
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,580
 I'm really sorry, I've ate all this food, you know.

151
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:07,840
 I don't have money to pay, please forgive me, right.

152
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,200
 And this man's just staring blankly at him like,

153
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,040
 why is this kid like confessing

154
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,240
 all his sins to me right now, you know.

155
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,200
 And then anyway, I was standing in the corner

156
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:19,400
 also crying, but with laughter, right.

157
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,340
 Like, I'm not saying it was a good thing or a bad thing,

158
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:25,220
 I don't know, but no more food was wasted that trip.

159
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,300
 We'll say it like that, okay.

160
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:31,300
 So, now of course, you know, that's a bit of a funny story.

161
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,900
 But in a way, we sort of, we've all been there, right,

162
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,700
 in that moment.

163
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:39,140
 Like that moment when we realize we've done something wrong

164
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:41,220
 and the guilt and the shame and the fear

165
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:42,880
 that comes with that.

166
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:43,980
 And then you have this reaction

167
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:45,420
 of trying to make things right.

168
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:48,140
 Realizing then, actually, there is nothing I can do

169
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:48,980
 to make it right.

170
00:05:48,980 --> 00:05:53,900
 The only thing left for me to do is to ask for forgiveness

171
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:57,220
 and hope that forgiveness is offered to us.

172
00:05:57,220 --> 00:06:01,400
 You know, we're at the tail end of the year already,

173
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,720
 believe it or not.

174
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:05,560
 And we have Advent starting soon.

175
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:08,520
 But before Advent, this is our last sermon series

176
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:09,760
 of the year.

177
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:12,640
 And actually, this sermon series was born

178
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:16,720
 out of a heart cry of the community, I believe.

179
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:18,840
 And you may remember a few months ago,

180
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,280
 we did an event called Converse.

181
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,240
 And at Converse, we set up prayer stations

182
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:25,200
 up at a high school, you know, just up the hill.

183
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,240
 And there was a big hall and there was all these different,

184
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,720
 amazing prayer stations, different ways for us

185
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,400
 to interact with prayer.

186
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:34,440
 And one of the stations was to do with forgiveness, right.

187
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,960
 It was either asking, you know, prayer requests

188
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:41,760
 to give forgiveness or to receive forgiveness.

189
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:44,920
 And as we looked through the prayer requests

190
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,480
 that were written out, we realized, right,

191
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:51,680
 this is a theme that so many of us are struggling with

192
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,820
 in our community.

193
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:56,680
 Many of these had to do with relationships, right.

194
00:06:56,680 --> 00:07:00,460
 People asking for the strength to be able to forgive people

195
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:03,120
 that have hurt them in different ways.

196
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,760
 There were also many voices asking for forgiveness

197
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:08,280
 because they have been the ones who have caused harm

198
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,720
 and hurt to other people.

199
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,560
 A lot of written on there was to, you know,

200
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:14,640
 about forgiving ourselves, right.

201
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,560
 The different things that we struggle with,

202
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,720
 asking God for forgiveness.

203
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:21,600
 And in some ways, there was also a lot of requests

204
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:25,120
 asking for, you know, to be able to forgive God, right.

205
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,320
 Because people have felt like God has let them down.

206
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,880
 They put their faith in God and they felt like God

207
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:29,720
 had let them down.

208
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:32,480
 And I feel like I need to forgive God in some way.

209
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:36,040
 And so since this was a topic that so many of us

210
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,520
 were wrestling with, we figured it was time

211
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:42,080
 to address this together as a church.

212
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:45,880
 Because the truth is, we all need, everyone needs

213
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:48,800
 to come to a good understanding of what forgiveness is,

214
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,680
 of what forgiveness is and what it's supposed to look like

215
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:55,800
 because forgiveness sits at the center of God's heart.

216
00:07:55,800 --> 00:08:00,520
 And forgiveness is essential for our relationship with God.

217
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,200
 In fact, without forgiveness, there would be no relationship

218
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,600
 with God possible, right.

219
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,320
 At the same time, forgiveness is also essential

220
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:11,240
 for us to be in relationship and in community

221
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,280
 with each other.

222
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:16,200
 Without forgiveness, not even this church, right,

223
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:19,040
 society itself would totally break down

224
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,800
 and we would never be able to do life

225
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,720
 and to connect with each other.

226
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:27,080
 But at the same time, as we've experienced,

227
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:30,080
 it's not that simple.

228
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,480
 Right, because forgiveness is nuanced

229
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:35,160
 with so many different questions and feelings and emotions.

230
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:37,440
 And over these next few weeks, we're gonna face

231
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,120
 some of these questions head on.

232
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,880
 We're gonna be talking about some theological framework

233
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:46,880
 about what forgiveness is from the biblical perspective.

234
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,400
 We're gonna be looking at some very practical ways

235
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,560
 of how we can forgive, what forgiveness is

236
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:53,480
 and what forgiveness isn't.

237
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:56,040
 We're gonna hear testimonies from our community groups

238
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:59,880
 about how forgiveness has been such an enriching part

239
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,640
 of their relationship with each other.

240
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,320
 We're gonna talk about what it means

241
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:06,400
 for us to forgive ourselves.

242
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,960
 And in the end, the hope is we're gonna be equipped

243
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,800
 to be live out, to be walking out,

244
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:15,320
 to live a life that is defined by forgiveness.

245
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,120
 And so to start us on our journey today,

246
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,840
 I want to look at a passage that teaches us,

247
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:22,720
 you know, that I think really Jesus uses this passage

248
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:26,280
 to highlight just how important forgiveness is

249
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,440
 from his perspective and how he hopes

250
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:31,400
 his followers will respond to it.

251
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,960
 Okay, we're looking at Matthew chapter 18, verses 21 to 35.

252
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:38,160
 I'm gonna read it and you can follow along.

253
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,160
 Then Peter came to Jesus and asked,

254
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:45,280
 "Lord, how many times shall I forgive my brother or sister

255
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,880
 "who sins against me?

256
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:49,440
 "Up to seven times?"

257
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:54,440
 Jesus answered, "I tell you, not seven times, but 77 times.

258
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:57,160
 "Therefore, the kingdom of heaven is like a king

259
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,920
 "who wanted to settle accounts with his servants.

