517
00:21:32,180 --> 00:21:35,720
 the harder I try, it's almost like the harder we fail.

518
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:38,540
 And I've slowly come to the realization

519
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:42,620
 that through our own power, through our own will,

520
00:21:42,620 --> 00:21:44,940
 we will never, ever, ever, ever be able

521
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:47,540
 to pay back the debt of sin.

522
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:54,140
 And the master realizes this and God realizes this.

523
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:55,900
 And even though he has the right and authority

524
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:58,900
 to divine some sort of payment,

525
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:01,560
 something really beautiful happens.

526
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:06,380
 This phrase, "The servant's master took pity on him."

527
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:08,460
 The word pity here means like love actually

528
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:10,120
 and compassion.

529
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:13,580
 Not because the servant has done anything

530
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:17,560
 to deserve a pardon, but because of the master's heart

531
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:21,380
 of love and compassion, the debt is canceled

532
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:23,020
 and he is set free.

533
00:22:23,020 --> 00:22:26,300
 And considering the amount of debt he was owed,

534
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:28,180
 this was unimaginable, right?

535
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,540
 The listeners of Jesus's time listening to this,

536
00:22:30,540 --> 00:22:32,560
 were like, "This guy must be crazy

537
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:35,460
 "to just let all that money go."

538
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:37,420
 But this is the master saying,

539
00:22:37,420 --> 00:22:39,620
 "What matters to me is not the amount of money

540
00:22:39,620 --> 00:22:43,720
 "that he owes, I'm trying to demonstrate my heart

541
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:47,900
 "of grace, of mercy, of compassion, and of love."

542
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:52,220
 And the servant walks away in freedom.

543
00:22:52,220 --> 00:22:56,100
 And this is Jesus reminding us, right?

544
00:22:56,100 --> 00:23:00,320
 This is an echo of God's message of forgiveness of sin.

545
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:02,100
 Actually, this is a message that God has said

546
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:04,660
 time and time and time again.

547
00:23:04,660 --> 00:23:06,620
 We see God's heart to forgive.

548
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:09,540
 Throughout the Old Testament even, Isaiah 43, 25,

549
00:23:09,540 --> 00:23:12,840
 "I will blot out your transgressions."

550
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:16,140
 Jeremiah 31, 34, "I will forgive their wickedness

551
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:18,500
 "and remember their sins no more."

552
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:21,620
 Psalm 103, 12, one of my favorite passages,

553
00:23:21,620 --> 00:23:24,140
 "As far the east is from the west,

554
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:29,140
 "so far has he removed our transgressions from us."

555
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:32,140
 This is our starting point, church.

556
00:23:32,140 --> 00:23:33,600
 Never forget this.

557
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:39,600
 God's heart is one that is inclined towards forgiveness.

558
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:43,120
 His heart is one of compassion and of love.

559
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,200
 This is what we were singing over and over

560
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:47,120
 and over again this morning, right?

561
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:50,400
 His heart is that despite the fact that we have wronged him,

562
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,920
 we have disappointed him, we have sinned in our lives,

563
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:56,040
 we have missed the mark, we have gone against his will,

564
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:59,040
 despite that many times we make a mess of things,

565
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:03,000
 God still looks on us with love and compassion, amen?

566
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
 And God loved us so much,

567
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:10,120
 he gave us his most precious gift, his son,

568
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:13,160
 as the only way to repay the debt of sin,

569
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:16,720
 God gave us his son, paying the debt of our sins

570
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:19,400
 so that we can have relationship with him.

571
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:21,600
 Again, this is something we're gonna talk more about

572
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,420
 next week and in the weeks to come.

573
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:27,360
 But what we need to understand for today is this,

574
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:30,800
 is we who worship the true God are a people

575
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:34,480
 who have had all their debt forgiven

576
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:37,360
 because our master loves us.

577
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,920
 Forgiveness, therefore, is important

578
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:43,640
 because it's the key not just to this life,

579
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:47,080
 but to eternal life as well.

580
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:48,760
 This is what I mean when I say forgiveness

581
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,440
 sits at the very heart of God

582
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:53,800
 and encapsulates all that he came to do,

583
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:58,640
 was to offer forgiveness for you, for me,

584
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,920
 for anyone who asks of it.

585
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:05,000
 If you are a follower of Jesus in this room today,

586
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:09,880
 you are free because you have received God's forgiveness.

587
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:14,080
 Now, as a people who've understood

588
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:17,440
 and experienced this wonderful gift of forgiveness,

589
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:20,760
 you would think that we would now want to share

590
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,720
 this gift with others as well,

591
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:25,520
 like last week when we were talking about the gospel.

592
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,960
 But again, it's hard and it's complicated.

593
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:31,280
 It doesn't always work this way.

594
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:32,760
 And for the servant on this story,

595
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:35,040
 we find that though, even though he is the one

596
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:38,440
 who has experienced the forgiveness of a great debt,

597
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:40,780
 his own heart remains unchanged.

598
00:25:40,780 --> 00:25:44,760
 It tells us this, but when that servant went out,

599
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,580
 he found one of his fellow servants

600
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:48,800
 who owed him 100 silver coins.

601
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,880
 He grabbed him and began to choke him.

602
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:53,760
 "Pay back what you owe me," he demanded.

603
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:56,860
 His fellow servant fell to his knees and begged him,

604
00:25:56,860 --> 00:26:00,680
 "Be patient with me and I will pay it back."

605
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:02,200
 But he refused.

606
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,480
 Instead, he went off and had that man thrown in prison

607
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,160
 until he could pay the debt.

608
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:12,080
 You see, when this man encounters someone who owes him money,

609
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,480
 his heart is not full of compassion.

610
00:26:14,480 --> 00:26:18,580
 He remains tight-fisted and stingy about what he's owed.

611
00:26:18,580 --> 00:26:22,440
 100 silver coins, okay, I said just now,

612
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:25,640
 you know that 10,000 bags of gold was like a gazillion

613
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:28,900
 dollars, 100 silver coins would have been about maybe

614
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:31,140
 the equivalent of four months' wages,

615
00:26:31,140 --> 00:26:32,560
 the Bible scholars say.

616
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,580
 Not a small sum in and of itself,

617
00:26:34,580 --> 00:26:37,520
 but not insurmountable as well.

618
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:42,520
 But compared to what he owed, completely insignificant.

619
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:45,580
 And this dialogue that he has, it's almost an exact replica

620
00:26:45,580 --> 00:26:49,140
 of what just happened with him and his master.

621
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:51,340
 There's a debt, there's a falling to the knees,

622
00:26:51,340 --> 00:26:54,000
 begging for patience and mercy.

623
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,760
 But like I said, the difference is that there's no mention

624
00:26:56,760 --> 00:27:00,120
 of compassion from this servant's heart.

625
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:02,420
 Instead, it's the opposite.

626
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:06,320
 Listen to this term, he said he refused.

627
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:09,420
 When it says refused, this word means to sort of like

628
00:27:09,420 --> 00:27:11,100
 harden his heart, right?

629
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:13,760
 He made a conscious decision in his mind,

630
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:16,680
 I am not willing, I'm going to make a choice

631
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:19,480
 not to forgive this person.

632
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,540
 And actually, it gets even worse.

633
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:25,360
 Not only does he refuse, but he tries to take actions

634
00:27:25,360 --> 00:27:27,140
 into his own hands.

635
00:27:27,140 --> 00:27:28,700
 He escalates.

636
00:27:28,700 --> 00:27:30,660
 He purposely, first of all, goes out of his way

637
00:27:30,660 --> 00:27:32,700
 to seek out this person who owes him.

638
00:27:32,700 --> 00:27:36,540
 And when he finds him, it says he physically abuses him.

639
00:27:36,540 --> 00:27:39,460
 He grabs him and he chokes him.

640
00:27:39,460 --> 00:27:41,640
 He takes matters into his own hands.

641
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:46,140
 As you read this story, you probably, as I was,

642
00:27:46,140 --> 00:27:47,780
 judging this guy right now.

643
00:27:47,780 --> 00:27:51,800
 Well, how evil, how wicked is this man

644
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:54,340
 that he would do something like this?

645
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:59,520
 Now, before we get too judgmental of the servant,

646
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:02,640
 and as uncomfortable as this might make us,

647
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,860
 maybe we need to lean into this part of the story

648
00:28:04,860 --> 00:28:06,220
 a little bit.

649
00:28:06,220 --> 00:28:08,140
 And I found it helpful, instead of judging it

650
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:12,800
 from the outside, to use this scenario more like a mirror

651
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:15,700
 to check my own attitude toward forgiveness.

652
00:28:16,540 --> 00:28:18,060
 Maybe it's a bit more like this servant

653
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:19,100
 than we think it is.

654
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:23,340
 Because like I said just now, when we've been sinned against

655
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:27,940
 our first reaction is more likely inclined towards revenge.

656
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:33,140
 We want to see people suffer and get what they deserve

657
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:34,520
 when they sin against us.

658
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:39,020
 I admit to you, in my own heart, this is often what I feel.

659
00:28:39,020 --> 00:28:41,380
 I want to be able to enjoy all of God's forgiveness.

660
00:28:41,380 --> 00:28:43,060
 Yes, I want to be able to come to God,

661
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:45,440
 ask for his forgiveness, and receive his compassion

662
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,420
 and mercy and grace.

663
00:28:47,420 --> 00:28:49,580
 But sometimes when people sin against me,

664
00:28:49,580 --> 00:28:52,140
 my first reaction is not, "Father, forgive them."

665
00:28:52,140 --> 00:28:54,300
 My reaction is, "I hope they suffer.

666
00:28:54,300 --> 00:28:59,120
 "I hope God punished them for what they did to me.

667
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,020
 "In fact, I hope they first, you know,

668
00:29:01,020 --> 00:29:04,040
 "they experience 10 times worse than what they did to me.

669
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:05,640
 "That's what they deserve."

670
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:09,240
 I know I'm not alone in this.

671
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:12,720
 But this is precisely why this whole series

672
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:16,180
 and this conversation on forgiveness is important

673
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:18,220
 for us to have together.

674
00:29:18,220 --> 00:29:22,580
 Because now Jesus starts to talk about the consequences,

675
00:29:22,580 --> 00:29:24,860
 about debt, when we don't forgive.

676
00:29:24,860 --> 00:29:29,300
 Jesus seems to be saying, "Unless you learn to forgive

677
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:31,440
 "that you have been forgiven,

678
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:34,100
 "there are gonna be consequences.

679
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:38,460
 "And these consequences affect both the wider community,

680
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:42,240
 "but also your own relationship with God as well."

681
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:46,020
 Let me tell you how it leaves a strain

682
00:29:46,020 --> 00:29:47,880
 on the community, first of all.

683
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,980
 When the other servants saw what had happened,

684
00:29:49,980 --> 00:29:52,960
 they were outraged and went and told their master

685
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:56,460
 everything that has happened, that had happened.

686
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:58,600
 All right, this is why I said

687
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:00,680
 this is a heart cry of the church.

688
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:03,060
 This is why I said we're gonna take this journey together

689
00:30:03,060 --> 00:30:05,040
 as a community, as a body of Christ,

690
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,500
 as a family of brothers and sisters.

691
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:10,240
 Because often when we talk about forgiveness,

692
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:14,080
 we tend to look at it individualistically.

693
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:16,160
 That's just between two people.

694
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:20,320
 It doesn't concern the rest of the community.

695
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,480
 So let's say me and Derek here had beef.

696
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:24,240
 We had a problem with each other.

697
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:28,680
 If people find out, just leave the Eric and,

698
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,600
 Ellison and Derek can figure that out by themselves,

699
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:32,160
 it doesn't concern us.

700
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:34,500
 But actually it does.

701
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:38,660
 I think as a body of Christ, we all need to agree

702
00:30:38,660 --> 00:30:41,600
 that forgiveness is a poison.

703
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:43,720
 And that if we don't deal with it,

704
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:46,560
 there is no way we can ever be the body of Christ

705
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:48,120
 that he has called us to be.

706
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:51,020
 How are we supposed to walk alongside each other

707
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:52,880
 if we're not willing to forgive?

708
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:55,100
 How are we supposed to grow in intimacy

709
00:30:55,100 --> 00:30:58,080
 if we hold grudges against each other?

710
00:30:58,080 --> 00:30:59,820
 How are we gonna encourage each other

711
00:30:59,820 --> 00:31:02,840
 if we keep account of what's right and what's wrong?

712
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,120
 Every time we've wronged and right,

713
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:07,000
 we keep an account of the rights and wrongs.

714
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:10,820
 Therefore, as a community, we need to be aware of this.

715
00:31:10,820 --> 00:31:14,980
 And as a community, if we see unforgiveness taking place,

716
00:31:14,980 --> 00:31:17,260
 we need to do something about it

717
00:31:17,260 --> 00:31:20,860
 so it doesn't corrupt the rest of the body of Christ.

718
00:31:20,860 --> 00:31:22,360
 We need to call it out.

719
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:25,220
 What also points out is the community then,

720
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:27,300
 it's supposed to be a place of safety

721
00:31:27,300 --> 00:31:28,900
 and of accountability.

722
00:31:28,900 --> 00:31:31,460
 You see, if no one else had got involved,

723
00:31:31,460 --> 00:31:34,140
 the servant would have got away with his actions.

724
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:36,260
 He would have got away with abusing his debtor,

725
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:37,840
 having him thrown in jail,

726
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:40,280
 punished for something like that.

727
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:42,760
 But notice, it was the other servants

728
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,520
 who called him out of his sin.

729
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:47,560
 It was the other servants, the community around him

730
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:48,800
 that flagged to the master,

731
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:51,480
 hey, something isn't quite right here.

732
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:55,160
 And we need to do and say something about it.

733
00:31:55,160 --> 00:32:01,200
 So when it comes to forgiveness,

734
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:03,480
 we see forgiveness and justice

735
00:32:03,480 --> 00:32:07,060
 is something that actually go hand in hand with each other.

736
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:10,620
 Forgiveness doesn't mean that one's causing harm

737
00:32:10,620 --> 00:32:13,080
 can just get away with it.

738
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:15,980
 But forgiveness is what happens when a community,

739
00:32:15,980 --> 00:32:18,860
 when somebody is wrong and the community around you

740
00:32:18,860 --> 00:32:20,580
 comes around you to support you,

741
00:32:20,580 --> 00:32:24,500
 to give you strength and power to confront the wrong

742
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:26,500
 and it's voiced out.

743
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:28,380
 You see what I'm saying?

744
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:30,900
 Community, I mean, forgiveness doesn't mean saying

745
00:32:30,900 --> 00:32:32,180
 it really didn't happen, right?

746
00:32:32,180 --> 00:32:35,260
 It really doesn't matter, just let it go, right?

747
00:32:35,260 --> 00:32:36,980
 In either of those cases, if it didn't matter,

748
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:40,020
 you just let it go, you don't need forgiveness, right?

749
00:32:40,020 --> 00:32:41,380
 Maybe it's just a misunderstanding

750
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:43,500
 that needs to be cleared up.

751
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:46,220
 But forgiveness is the process when we admit,

752
00:32:46,220 --> 00:32:48,900
 yes, something did happen.

753
00:32:48,900 --> 00:32:51,660
 It did matter, something has gone wrong

754
00:32:51,660 --> 00:32:54,100
 and we need to deal with it.

755
00:32:54,100 --> 00:32:57,620
 And we deal with it together as a body of Christ.

756
00:32:57,620 --> 00:33:00,100
 But the way we deal with it is to hand it over to God,

757
00:33:00,100 --> 00:33:01,900
 to say we're not God.

758
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:05,540
 We don't get to set the standard of who is worthy

759
00:33:05,540 --> 00:33:07,580
 of forgiveness or who is not.

760
00:33:07,580 --> 00:33:11,820
 We simply offer forgiveness first

761
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:15,340
 because without that, we will never be able to move on

762
00:33:15,340 --> 00:33:17,900
 as individuals and as a community.

763
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:23,500
 So that's how it affects us together as a body of Christ.

764
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:27,500
 On the same time though, it has an individual impact

765
00:33:27,500 --> 00:33:29,460
 on us as well.

766
00:33:29,460 --> 00:33:31,100
 And God spells out very clearly

767
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:33,540
 the results of withholding forgiveness.

768
00:33:33,540 --> 00:33:37,220
 Then the master called the servant in.

769
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:39,540
 You wicked servant, he said.

770
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:44,500
 I canceled all that debt of yours because you begged me to.

771
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:47,200
 Shouldn't you have had mercy on your fellow servant

772
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:49,540
 just as I had on you?

773
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:52,020
 In his anger, the master handed him over to the jailers

774
00:33:52,020 --> 00:33:56,300
 to be tortured until he should pay back all that he owed.

775
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:59,260
 This is how my heavenly father will treat each of you

776
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:04,140
 unless you forgive your brother or sister from your heart.

777
00:34:04,140 --> 00:34:07,640
 Again, this sounds harsh.

778
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:10,820
 But I think the point Scripture is trying to make is this.

779
00:34:10,820 --> 00:34:14,060
 It might seem like when we don't offer forgiveness

780
00:34:14,060 --> 00:34:18,180
 that we hold onto the power, that we hold onto the control.

781
00:34:18,180 --> 00:34:20,100
 But when in reality, what Jesus is saying

782
00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:22,680
 is when we withhold forgiveness,

783
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:25,440
 it's actually a great detriment to us.

784
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:28,700
 It seems like the other person

785
00:34:28,700 --> 00:34:30,660
 is getting what they deserve.

786
00:34:30,660 --> 00:34:34,300
 But in reality, what we're doing is condemning ourselves.

787
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:37,100
 You might know the old saying,

788
00:34:37,100 --> 00:34:39,340
 unforgiveness is like drinking a poison

789
00:34:39,340 --> 00:34:41,300
 and expecting the other person to die.

790
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:46,980
 Right, so it has really, really serious consequences

791
00:34:46,980 --> 00:34:50,340
 for ourselves if we withhold forgiveness.

792
00:34:50,340 --> 00:34:52,940
 Maybe you could think about it this way.

793
00:34:52,940 --> 00:34:55,820
 All right, we're gonna do a little exercise together.

794
00:34:55,820 --> 00:34:57,120
 Okay, on the count of three,

795
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:59,340
 I want everybody to take a deep breath.

796
00:34:59,340 --> 00:35:00,820
 When you take a deep breath,

797
00:35:00,820 --> 00:35:03,260
 hold it in for as long as you can.

798
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:05,340
 Try and hold your breath.

799
00:35:05,340 --> 00:35:08,100
 One, two, three.

800
00:35:08,100 --> 00:35:25,780
 Some of us might be able to do this for longer.

801
00:35:25,780 --> 00:35:28,280
 But you're probably feeling a struggle to breathe now,

802
00:35:28,280 --> 00:35:31,680
 right, to breathe out that breath.

803
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:33,880
 Right, none of us, nobody in this room

804
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:36,320
 is able to hold their breath forever.

805
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,360
 You would either pass out,

806
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:39,920
 or if you really did just stop breathing altogether,

807
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:40,760
 you would die.

808
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:45,220
 In order for you to take your next breath,

809
00:35:45,220 --> 00:35:48,240
 you have to release the breath you're holding.

810
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:51,800
 And so it is with forgiveness.

811
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:56,260
 If we want to receive forgiveness,

812
00:35:56,260 --> 00:36:00,040
 we need to be able to release forgiveness to others as well.

813
00:36:00,040 --> 00:36:07,620
 Like I said, though, this is the starting point.

814
00:36:07,620 --> 00:36:10,700
 Right, this is just the introduction to this journey.

815
00:36:10,700 --> 00:36:13,500
 And there's no way we can unpack and discover

816
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:16,740
 all the things that forgiveness means for us

817
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:19,860
 in one short sermon on a Sunday morning.

818
00:36:20,820 --> 00:36:23,760
 So I want to encourage everybody here.

819
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:25,600
 Please try to come along, right,

820
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:28,040
 to the next few messages that we have,

821
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,700
 to the next few Sundays that we have

822
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:32,520
 in this journey of forgiveness.

823
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:33,560
 And this is not about, you know,

824
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:35,160
 like maintaining numbers at the Vine

825
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:38,180
 or anything like that, right, it's not about that.

826
00:36:38,180 --> 00:36:40,600
 But what this is, is it's for your wholeness.

827
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:42,280
 It's for your understanding.

828
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,520
 It's for you to really be able to embrace

829
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,100
 what forgiveness means,

830
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:49,940
 so you can walk in the freedom of forgiveness.

831
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:53,240
 After all, Jesus taught us to pray.

832
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:58,060
 Forgive our sins as we forgive those

833
00:36:58,060 --> 00:37:00,260
 who have sinned against us.

834
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:07,380
 And my heart is, as individuals, but also as a community,

835
00:37:07,380 --> 00:37:10,820
 we will embrace this journey of forgiveness together.

836
00:37:10,820 --> 00:37:13,460
 To step by step, learn what it means

837
00:37:13,460 --> 00:37:16,900
 to receive and to give out

838
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:19,460
 what forgiveness really means in God's heart.

839
00:37:20,300 --> 00:37:23,380
 This is how we build, continue the kingdom of God

840
00:37:23,380 --> 00:37:24,620
 here on this earth.

841
00:37:24,620 --> 00:37:29,420
 So would you pray with me as we start this journey together?

842
00:37:29,420 --> 00:37:47,260
 Jesus, we know that this is an issue

843
00:37:47,260 --> 00:37:49,020
 that many of us are wrestling with.

844
00:37:50,020 --> 00:37:53,500
 And even if we're not wrestling with it right at this moment

845
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:56,820
 there is gonna come a time where we've been wronged

846
00:37:56,820 --> 00:37:58,780
 and we need to offer forgiveness.

847
00:37:58,780 --> 00:38:02,540
 Or someone wrongs us, or we wrong someone else

848
00:38:02,540 --> 00:38:05,760
 and we need to be forgiven.

849
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:11,860
 And so Lord, I thank you that.

850
00:38:11,860 --> 00:38:14,980
 Our starting point, Lord, is that you have already

851
00:38:14,980 --> 00:38:17,680
 poured forgiveness out for us.

852
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:20,620
 That you have offered forgiveness to us despite our sin,

853
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:23,580
 despite the ways that we've missed the mark

854
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:26,420
 when it comes to being in relationship with you, Lord.

855
00:38:26,420 --> 00:38:31,200
 You've given us everything we need.

856
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:35,260
 Your most precious gift so that we can have forgiveness.

857
00:38:35,260 --> 00:38:39,240
 Lord, as we receive this gift, Lord,

858
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:45,380
 we hear that you've also asked us to pour it out

859
00:38:45,380 --> 00:38:47,000
 to those who have wronged us.

860
00:38:47,580 --> 00:38:52,580
 And I know this is a hard journey for some of us to take.

861
00:38:52,580 --> 00:38:58,620
 You know, you might be thinking right now,

862
00:38:58,620 --> 00:39:02,440
 if you only knew the pain that I've been through,

863
00:39:02,440 --> 00:39:06,760
 what this person did to me, how that person hurt me.

864
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:14,420
 And Father, we know that you meet us

865
00:39:14,420 --> 00:39:15,820
 in those areas of pain.

866
00:39:16,820 --> 00:39:19,680
 (soft music)

867
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:23,480
 And so Jesus, I pray that through your gentle guidance

868
00:39:23,480 --> 00:39:26,280
 in the way that only you know how you would teach us

869
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:30,100
 how to forgive.

870
00:39:30,100 --> 00:39:34,960
 That as we embrace forgiveness in our own hearts,

871
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:36,560
 it would soften our hearts.

872
00:39:42,440 --> 00:39:47,160
 And as we learn to live a life defined by forgiveness,

873
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:49,280
 we will reflect your gospel, your grace,

874
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,820
 your mercy to everybody.

875
00:39:50,820 --> 00:39:55,220
 And that even together as a community,

876
00:39:55,220 --> 00:39:58,860
 we can keep encouraging each other in this journey.

877
00:39:58,860 --> 00:40:02,980
 Keep encouraging each other to not keep things hidden,

878
00:40:02,980 --> 00:40:06,440
 but to bring it out into the light when there's been sin,

879
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:08,040
 when there's been wrong in the community.

880
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:13,040
 We will not let that just be swept under the carpet.

881
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:15,040
 But Lord, because we know the proper way

882
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:19,400
 to deal with these things, we can walk with it together.

883
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:25,400
 And that this forgiveness that we offer to each other

884
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:29,120
 reflects, truly reflects the heart that you have for us.

885
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:33,780
 So Lord, be with us in these next few weeks

886
00:40:33,780 --> 00:40:35,520
 as we walk through this.

887
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:37,580
 Encourage us, strengthen us, guide us.

888
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:40,940
 We pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

